      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:2:74:2",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " لَا تَكُونُ الْمُلَاعَنَةُ وَ لَا الْإِيلَاءُ إِلَّا بَعْدَ الدُّخُولِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Al Husayn Bin Muhammad, from Moala Bin Muhammad, from Al Hassan Bin Ali, from Aban, from Muhammad Bin Muslim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Neither does cursing happen, nor the swearing except after the copulation’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. Al-Husayn from Muhammad has narrated from Mu‘alla’ ibn Muhammad from al-Hassan ibn Ali from Aban from Muhammad ibn Muslim who has said the following: “Abu Ja‘far, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Condemnation and swearing take place only after going to bed with her.’” "
        ]
      }
